FIPS Codes for U.S. States

Source: R/fips.R
fips.Rd

This dataset provides Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) codes for U.S. states.

Usage

fips

Format

A data frame with 52 rows and 3 variables:

state

The name of the U.S. state (e.g., "Alabama").

state_code

The two-digit FIPS code for the state (e.g., "01").

state_name

The full name of the state (e.g., "Alabama").

Source

Derived from U.S. Census Bureau data.

Details

This dataset maps state FIPS codes to their names and abbreviations.

Examples

# Load the dataset
data(fips)

# View the first few rows
head(fips)
#>     state state_code state_name
#> 1      AL         01    Alabama
#> 68     AK         02     Alaska
#> 97     AZ         04    Arizona
#> 112    AR         05   Arkansas
#> 187    CA         06 California
#> 245    CO         08   Colorado

# Get FIPS code for a specific state
subset(fips, state == "California")
#> [1] state      state_code state_name
#> <0 rows> (or 0-length row.names)
